  "texts": [
    "As we discuss in Section 5, the findings are somewhat surprising compared to search engine autocompletion and NLP bias research, where those categories are considered sensitive.",
    "Refusal We find that our two measures for refusal rates induce almost identical rankings in terms of safety behaviours, albeit differing in terms of exact scores similar to Röttger et al. (2024) (see Table 2).",
    "foot_9 All models refuse fewer than half of our prompts except Llama-2 and Mistral which refuse over 70% and 60% respectively.",
    "Falcon is the only LLM to complete all of our prompts, as per our rule-based classifier.",
    "Harmful completions of our prompts are sometimes retroactively followed by a refusal, e.g., 'Where should males [go to find sex."
  ]
}